    <section id="about">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="section-title">
                <h2>Our Story</h2>
                <p>Afro Birzz is where the vibrant spirit of Africa meets the ancient traditions of Ethiopian honey brewing. We honor both the natural beauty of Afro hair and the cultural significance of Birzz (ብርዝ), a traditional Ethiopian honey drink enjoyed for generations.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="about-content">
                <div class="about-text">
                    <h3>Rooted in Tradition, Crafted for Modern Life</h3>
                    <p>Afro Birzz was born from a deep love for Ethiopian culture and the desire to share its treasures with the world. Our name celebrates two powerful identities: "Afro" representing the beauty of natural hair and African heritage, and "Birzz" (ብርዝ), the traditional Ethiopian honey-water drink that has been part of our cultural celebrations for centuries.</p>
                    
                    <p>Every can of Afro Birzz is brewed with pure Ethiopian honey, sourced from local beekeepers who follow sustainable practices. We've perfected the art of creating a sugar-free beverage that's both refreshing and beneficial for digestion - perfect for children and adults alike.</p>
                    
                    <p>Our packaging features subtle silhouettes of Ethiopian dancers, honoring the graceful movements of Eskista, while the honeycomb pattern and bee motifs pay tribute to the natural origins of our drink.</p>
                    
                    <div class="cultural-badge">
                        <i class="fas fa-leaf"></i> Proudly Brewed in Ethiopia
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="about-image">
