    <!-- Cultural Section -->
    <section id="culture" class="cultural-section">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="section-title">
                <h2>Cultural Celebration</h2>
                <p>Afro Birzz is more than a drink - it's a celebration of Ethiopian heritage and African identity</p>
            </div>
            <div class="cultural-content">
                <div class="cultural-text">
                    <h2>The Spirit of Birzz</h2>
                    <p>In Ethiopian tradition, Birzz (ብርዝ) is more than just a honey beverage - it's a symbol of hospitality, community, and celebration. Served during festivals and gatherings, it represents the sweetness of life and the bonds that connect us.</p>
                    
                    <p>Our brand name "Afro Birzz" intentionally celebrates two powerful cultural identities: "Afro" representing the beauty and pride of natural hair and African heritage, and "Birzz" connecting us to Ethiopian tradition. This fusion creates a unique beverage experience that honors both our past and present.</p>
                    
                    <p>The subtle dancer silhouettes on our packaging are inspired by the graceful movements of Eskista, Ethiopia's traditional shoulder dance. These elegant figures represent the joy, rhythm, and cultural expression that flows through our community.</p>
                    
                    <p>Every can features the phrase "Proudly Brewed in Ethiopia" - a testament to our commitment to authenticity and cultural pride. When you drink Afro Birzz, you're not just enjoying a beverage - you're participating in a centuries-old tradition of celebration and community.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="cultural-image">
                    <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1596025682466-3906e0c486a3?ixlib=rb-4.0.3&auto=format&fit=crop&w=800&q=80" alt="Ethiopian cultural celebration">
                    <div class="dance-motif">
                        <i class="fas fa-drum"></i>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

